						<BR><B>THIS MONTH'S ASSIGNMENT</B>			
						
						<P>Quick! You have only three more days until the next 
						"Your Assignment" deadline on January 10, 2003!

						<P>Each month <B>Writer's Digest</B> presents a creative challenge 
						for fun and prizes. Should you choose to accept our 
						assignment, submit your entry, typed on one side of a 
						standard-size postcard, to Your Assignment #156, Writer's 
						Digest, 4700 E. Galbraith Road, Cincinnati, OH 45236. 
						Include your name and address. The winner will receive 
						a selection of <B>Writer's Digest Books</B> worth approximately 
						$100, chosen by the editors of <B>Writer's Digest Magazine</B>. 

						<P><B>Your Assignment #156:</B> Think of an article, story, etc., 
						that you've written and draft a query or cover letter 
						submitting your work to a completely inappropriate 
						magazine. Cite absurd reasons why your work should be 
						an exception and why the editors should publish it in 
						their magazine. Don't forget to keep your entry to 75 
						words or less (including title).
						 
						<P><a href="http://www.writersdigest.com/specialoffers.asp?assignment010703">Click here for more information on this month's assignment</a>.
						
						



